PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1783727306
OL,3,CMan, 26, arrested on suspicion of
OL,4,Cmurder after ex-MP Ann Widdecombe
OL,5,Cfound dead
OL,7,FAddressing reporters, Starmer said he
OL,8,Fwould not speculate on any potential
OL,9,Fmotive but urged the public to help
OL,10,Fcatch the "clearly dangerous" suspect.
OL,12,FConservative leader Badenoch said:
OL,13,F"I've really struggled to find the
OL,14,Fwords to say. Ann Widdecombe was a
OL,15,Fvery fun and feisty woman who spoke
OL,16,Fher mind, and she was 78 years old,
OL,17,Fshe was an elderly woman.
OL,26,@rD@KOUrD@]O]uD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1783727306
OL,3,CMan, 26, arrested on suspicion of
OL,4,Cmurder after ex-MP Ann Widdecombe
OL,5,Cfound dead
OL,7,F"I don't understand how someone could
OL,8,Fdo something so horrific to an elderly
OL,9,Fperson. It was a nasty, horrific
OL,10,Fattack and my heart is breaking for
OL,11,Fher family."
OL,13,FReform UK leader Nigel Farage said he
OL,14,Fwas "deeply, deeply upset" by the
OL,15,Fnature of Ann Widdecombe's death.
OL,17,FIn a message shared on social media,
OL,18,Fthe Reform leader said: "I'm pleased
OL,19,Fthe police have caught somebody, a 26-
OL,20,Fyear-old man.
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@LO]vD@EOUvD@ZO]zD@YOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1783727306
OL,3,CMan, 26, arrested on suspicion of
OL,4,Cmurder after ex-MP Ann Widdecombe
OL,5,Cfound dead
OL,7,F"We don't know what political motives
OL,8,Fare, whether they exist at all. Was it
OL,9,Fa burglary gone wrong? We just don't
OL,10,Fknow. And I'm not going to speculate
OL,11,Fat this stage. I'm pleased the police
OL,12,Fare doing their job.
OL,14,F"Our nation is a much, much poorer
OL,15,Fplace without her. Reform UK is
OL,16,Fcertainly a much worse place without
OL,17,Fher. I was expecting to see her in
OL,18,FClacton over the course of the next
OL,19,Ffew days. Sadly, that is not going to
OL,20,Fhappen.
OL,26,@oD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1783727306
OL,3,CMan, 26, arrested on suspicion of
OL,4,Cmurder after ex-MP Ann Widdecombe
OL,5,Cfound dead
OL,7,F"And I do fear that for anybody in
OL,8,Fpublic life, or especially the
OL,9,Fpolitical space, things have become
OL,10,Feven more dangerous to them."
OL,12,FFarage added it was a "terrible
OL,13,Freflection on modern Britain".
OL,15,FA spokeswoman for Andy Burnham said:
OL,16,F"Andy's deepest condolences and
OL,17,Fthoughts are with Ann's family today,
OL,18,Fin incredibly distressing
OL,19,Fcircumstances.
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@]O]tD@WOUuD@]O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/16
